#IT Project: Phone Repair - Screen Replacement

### Device Information

Model : iPhone XR
Issue : Unresponsive touch and Cracked Screen

### Tools & Materials

-iPhone XR Screen Replacement
- Precision tools:
    - Y000 screw
    - Phillips screw
- 2 plastic opening picks
- Plastic spudger
- Waterproof Seal
- Tweezers
- Suction cup

### Troubleshooting & Diagnosis

Inspected the device for physical damage and identified a cracked screen along with minor keyboard/touch issues in the bottom-right corner of the display. The user stated that phone was dropped right before the screen became unresponsive. 
Tested the touchscreen functionality and confirmed that there was no screen response; only the side buttons were operational. Restarted the device to rule out a potential software malfunction. All internal components appeared to work properly, but the touch screen remain unresponsive after reboot.

### Repair Process

1. Waited for the phone to die - power needs to be off the device
2. Removed the two bottom pentalobe screws from the bottom of the phone
3. Apply heat around the edges of the screen with a blow dryer to loosen the adhesive 
4. Carefully separated display using a plastic guitar pick and a suction cup
5. Lifted the screen from the side (like and open book) and placed heavy object behind the screen for support to prevent for it to damage flex cables
6. Remove the three tri-wing screws that were securing the battery connector backet
7. Disconnected battery and display flex cables that  hold the battery bracket and lift the bracket with tweezers
8. Disconnected the battery cable using a plastic spudger
9. Removed the screws holding the display and top shield 
10. Disconnected the front sensor and ear speaker cable and carefully remove the screen from the phone
11. Removed any old adhesive from the frame and cleaned away dust/debris
12. Applied new adhesive around the edges of the phone
13. From the old screen, I removed screws holding the ear speaker assembly
14. Removed small sensor bracket and carefully remove the proximity sensor, ambient light sensor and front microphone
15. Transferred these part to the new screen and begin reassembling everything back to place
16. Positioned the new screen next to the phone and reconnect all the cables
17. Reinstalled all the screws and remove the adhesive film
18. Aligned the top screen with the phone and press around all the edges
19. Reinstalled the two bottom screws and turn the phone on
20. Tested the touchscreen response and other feature necessary

https://youtu.be/T-Hxa_NzP8w?si=PnnTsI5-Tj1nGu2B

### Testing & Results
The device was successfully connected and restored. Touchscreen responsiveness, brightness, and color display were tested and confirmed to be working properly. 
The device was powered normally and the user was able to access their data without any issues.

### Challenges Encountered
- Removing excess adhesive carefully to avoid damaging internal components
- Removing and organizing small screws during the disassembly process

